Edition:
Quote:  <i>Topknot:</i> Wool shorn from the top of a sheep's head. <i>Ibid.</i> <i>Wigging:</i> Shearing wool from the head of sheep. Normally carried out at crutching. The trade term for this wool is eye clips. Also known as topknots or wigs.
